Phase 4 — Dashboard

Phases 1-3 are complete. Platform foundation, plugin data/strategy layer, and trading engine all work. engine.py btc_15m runs, observes markets, writes observations, feeds the Observatory. Now build the dashboard so everything is visible and controllable.

Read PLATFORM_REFACTOR.md, DASHBOARD_UPDATE.md, and FLASK_STARTER_KIT.md for architecture and patterns. Read the old dashboard at /opt/15-min-btc-bot/dashboard.py (~13,560 lines) OR legacy/dashboard.py for complete implementation reference — copy the UI code and adapt it, don’t rewrite from scratch. The visual design and UX are battle-tested for mobile.

Notes from previous phases:

- plugin_state uses state_json blob. get_plugin_state returns {“status”, “status_detail”, “state”: {…}, “last_updated”}. The “state” dict contains all the dynamic fields (active_trade, live_market, bankroll_cents, lifetime_pnl, etc.)
- Plugin API routes prefixed /api/btc_15m/
- Platform API routes have no prefix: /api/state, /api/config, /api/command, /api/logs, etc.
- Config is namespaced: btc_15m.trading_mode in DB, but load_config() strips prefix so plugin code uses “trading_mode”
- No localStorage anywhere — iOS PWA constraint
- The current toast uses translucent backdrop-filter blur with rgba backgrounds and color-coded borders (green, red, yellow, blue, orange, purple). See FLASK_STARTER_KIT.md for the exact implementation.

Core design rule: FIVE tabs always: Trades, Regimes, Home, Stats, Settings. Platform owns these tabs. Plugins provide COMPONENTS that get composed INTO them. Never duplicate tabs. With one plugin, the dashboard looks identical to the old app.

